org.jamwiki.parser

Class ParserOutput

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jamwiki.parser.ParserOutput
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class ParserOutput
extends Object
implements Serializable
    This class represents the output from the JAMWiki parser. It holds parsed output text as well as metadata that is generated by the parser.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      static ParserOutput IMMUTABLE_PARSER_OUTPUT
      For performance reasons provide a static ParserOutput object that cannot be modified, changed, and thus has no memory impacts.

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Reset this ParserOutput instance to its default state.

      • addCategory

        public void addCategory(String categoryName,
                        String sortKey)
        When a document contains a token indicating that the document belongs to a specific category this method should be called to add that category to the output metadata.
        Parameters:
        categoryName - The name of the category that the document belongs to.
        sortKey - The sort key for the category, or null if no sort key has been specified. The sort key determines what order categories are sorted on category index pages, so a category for "John Doe" might be given a sort key of "Doe, John".

      • addInterwikiLink

        public void addInterwikiLink(String interwikiLink)
        Add a fully-formatted interwiki link to the list of available interwiki links for a document. These links can then be rendered separately from the document, for example in an "Other Sites" toolbox.
        Parameters:
        interwikiLink - The fully-formatted HTML interwiki link.

      • addLink

        public void addLink(String topicName)
        When a document contains a token indicating that the document links to another Wiki topic this method should be called to add that topic link to the output metadata.
        Parameters:
        topicName - The name of the topic that is linked to.

      • addTemplate

        public void addTemplate(String template)
        When a document contains a token indicating that the document includes a Wiki template this method should be called to add that template to the output metadata.
        Parameters:
        template - The name of the template that is being included.

      • addVirtualWikiLink

        public void addVirtualWikiLink(String virtualWikiLink)
        Add a fully-formatted virtual wiki link to the list of available virtual wiki links for a document. These links can then be rendered separately from the document, for example in an "Other Languages" toolbox.
        Parameters:
        virtualWikiLink - The fully-formatted HTML interwiki link.

      • getCacheable

        public boolean getCacheable()
        Return a flag indicating whether or not the current ParserOutput object can be cached. If the document contains user-specific, time-specific or other non-cacheable content then this method should return false.
        Returns:
        true if the current ParserOutput is cacheable, false if it contains any non-cacheable content.

      • setCacheable

        public void setCacheable(boolean cacheable)
        Sets a flag indicating whether or not the current ParserOutput object can be cached. If the document contains user-specific, time-specific or other non-cacheable content then the cacheable flag should be set to false.
        Parameters:
        cacheable - Set to true if the current ParserOutput is cacheable, false if it contains any non-cacheable content.

      • getCategories

        public Map<String,String> getCategories()
        Return the current mapping of categories associated with the document being parsed. The mapping contains key-value pairs with the category name as the key and the sort key (if any) as the value.
        Returns:
        A mapping of categories and their associated sort keys (if any) for all categories that are associated with the document being parsed.

      • getInterwikiLinks

        public List<String> getInterwikiLinks()
        For the document being parsed, return the current list of interwiki links for all interwiki links specified for the current document.
        Returns:
        A list of all interwiki links for all interwiki links specified for the current document.

      • getLinks

        public List<String> getLinks()
        For the document being parsed, return the current list of topic names for all topics that are linked to from the current document.
        Returns:
        A list of all topic names that are linked to from the current document.

      • getPageTitle

        public String getPageTitle()
        If a parser element supports setting an alternate page title then this field provides a way to do so. If no alternate page title is specified then this method should return null.
        Returns:
        An alternate page title as indicated by a parsing element, or null if no alternate page title is specified.

      • setPageTitle

        public void setPageTitle(String pageTitle)
        If a parser element supports setting an alternate page title then this field provides a way to do so. If no alternate page title is specified then this method should return null.
        Parameters:
        pageTitle - An alternate page title as indicated by a parsing element, or null if no alternate page title is in use.

      • getSectionName

        public String getSectionName()
        When editing or parsing a section of a document, get the name of the heading for that section.
        Returns:
        The name of the heading for a section of a document being parsed, or null if a section is not being parsed. If not null then the section name should be encoded for use in a URL.

      • setSectionName

        public void setSectionName(String sectionName)
        When editing or parsing a section of a document, set the name of the heading for that section.
        Parameters:
        sectionName - The name of the heading for a section of a document being parsed, or null if a section is not being parsed. If not null then the section name should be encoded for use in a URL.

      • getTemplates

        public List<String> getTemplates()
        For the document being parsed, return the current list of templates names for all templates that are included in the current document.
        Returns:
        A list of all template names that are included in the current document.

      • getRedirect

        public String getRedirect()
        If a document being parsed represents a redirect, return the name of the topic that this document redirects to.
        Returns:
        The name of the topic that this document redirects to, or null if the document does not represent a redirect.
